  <div id="health_and_safety" class="d-flex justify-content-center align-items-center">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="row justify-content-center description">
        <div class="col-12 col-lg-6">
          <h4>Covid-19 Information</h4>
          <div>
            The health and safety of our attendees, educators, and staff is our top priority. Based on guidance from the CDC, health authorities, and local Denver law, we have implemented the following safety measures to provide all attendees with the safest experience possible:
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-12 col-lg-6 list">
          <div class="mb-3">• To enter the venue, all attendees must either provide proof of vaccination (dated no later than May 1st, 2022) OR proof of a negative COVID-19 test taken within 72 hours of first Sessions experience, along with a government-issued photo ID. In addition to a negative test, we also ask that all non-vaccinated attendees wear a mask when inside the venue.</div>
          <div class="mb-3">• Full vaccination is defined as 14 days since your second dose of the Pfizer-BioNtech or Moderna COVID-19 vaccine, or a single dose of the Johnson & Johnson vaccine.</div>
          <div class="mb-3">• There will be ongoing cleaning services with EPA registered products and ample hand sanitizing stations throughout the venue.</div>
          <div class="mb-3">• We ask that you not attend if: Within 14 days prior to the event, you have tested positive or been exposed to someone who has tested positive for COVID-19; within 48 hours prior to the event, you have experienced symptoms of COVID-19; or within 14 days of the event, you have traveled to any international territory that is subject to travel or quarantine restrictions.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="polka-dot"></div>
  </div>

